Demonstration of vector derived datatype

MPI_Type_vector creates a new type of equally spaced identicall blocks.

It's useful when you want to send data that isn't contiguous, like a column of
a 2D array, or every Nth element, which is "regularly spaced".


    int MPI_Type_vector(
        int count,          // number of blocks
        int blocklength,    // number of elements in each block
        int stride,         // displacement between the blocks
        MPI_Datatype oldtype,
        MPI_Datatype *newtype // the new data type (has to be committed)
    );

Remember to call

    MPI_Type_commit(&newtype);
  before using it, and
    MPI_Type_free(&newtype)
  when done.


Example:

    MPI_Type_vector(3, 2, 3, oldtype, newtype);

    oldtype [x]

                     blocklen=2
                     <---->
    newtype [x][x][ ][x][x][ ][x][x][ ]
            <------->
             stride=3

    3 sets of (two-elements, skip 1)

    i.e., start somewhere take 2 elements, hop three elements, take 2 elements,
    hop three elements, take 2 elements.
